PRETORIA The Absa Premiership match between Mamelodi Sundowns and Chippa United at Loftus was abandoned on Tuesday night.With the score goalless after 41 minutes, the floodlights went out because of a power failure.The power failure affected Loftus and the surrounding areas. The information relayed to officials was that it would take more than two hours to fix the problem. As a result, the match was called off and will replayed at a later date. African News Agency